I"²<h1 id="power-of-two">Power of Two</h1>
<p>Given an integer n, return true if it is a power of two. Otherwise, return false.</p>

<p>An integer n is a power of two, if there exists an integer x such that n == 2x.</p>

<h5 id="example-1">Example 1:</h5>
<div class="language-markdown highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Input: n = 1
Output: true
Explanation: 20 = 1
</code></pre></div></div>
<h5 id="example-2">Example 2:</h5>
<div class="language-markdown highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Input: n = 16
Output: true
Explanation: 24 = 16
</code></pre></div></div>
<h5 id="example-3">Example 3:</h5>
<div class="language-markdown highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Input: n = 3
Output: false
</code></pre></div></div>
<h5 id="constraints">Constraints:</h5>
<ul>
  <li>-231 &lt;= n &lt;= 231 - 1</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="solution">Solution</h3>
:ET